(in-progress):
  * Refactor core into libmodemu2k; public API in modemu2k.h at project root
  * Remove gettext/NLS support and translations
  * Fix connecting via hostname when the first resolved address fails, e.g.
    localhost resolving to ::1 before 127.0.0.1 (issue #44)
  * Add TCP listen mode (-l/--listen <port>) intended for use as a virtual
    modem backend for emulators such as dosemu2 (issue #32)
  * Print --help output and exit when invoked with no arguments
  * Reject conflicting -c/-d/-l/-s combinations at parse time instead of
    silently honoring the last one
  * Wrap modemu2k.h declarations in extern "C" guards for C++ consumers
  * Sync license claim to GPL-2-or-later (matches the source headers)
  * Add steppable event-loop API (m2k_get_pollfds, m2k_step, m2k_run_done)
    plus embed-mode I/O (m2k_setup_app_io, m2k_write_from_app,
    m2k_read_to_app) so a host program can run modemu2k inside its own
    poll/epoll loop with the host supplying the TTY-side bytes
  * Add m2k_set_error_buffer() for curl-style per-context detailed error
    messages, plus M2K_ERR_AT and M2K_ERR_FULL error codes

2022-08-18
- modemu2k (v0.1.0)
  * fix segfault when building with Slackbuild or setting buildtype to debug
  * fix build on macos (timeval errors, see
    https://github.com/theimpossibleastronaut/modemu2k/pull/40)
  * fix connecting to host using IP
  * replaced autotools build system with mesonbuild
  * 'm2k-minicom.sh' script renamed to 'm2k-minicom'

